This paper focuses on the development of a new approach for conditional generative models, which is a popular topic in machine learning. The paper proposes a new model called CompVAE, which learns a latent representation leveraging both observational and symbolic information. This suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed approach to synthetic 1D and 2D problems, which could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
